│ code patterns, I found that the standard approach is to use                 │
│ `changeToUnreachable` followed by proper cleanup, but the key insight is    │
│ that the order of operations matters.                                       │
│                                                                             │
│ Looking at other LLVM passes, I notice that they typically:                 │
│ 1. Mark dead blocks as unreachable                                          │
│ 2. Remove non-feasible edges                                                │
│ 3. Delete dead blocks                                                       │
│ 4. Then perform function-level optimizations                                │
│                                                                             │
│ The issue in the current code is that function specialization (which        │
│ deletes functions) is happening before all dead blocks are properly         │
